The most common bug to avoid in this task is incorrectly handling the case where the input list is already the last permutation, resulting in an infinite loop or incorrect output. 

```python
def next_permutation(xs):
    i = len(xs) - 2
    while i >= 0 and xs[i] >= xs[i + 1]:
        i -= 1
    if i < 0:
        xs.reverse()
    else:
        j = len(xs) - 1
        while xs[j] <= xs[i]:
            j -= 1
        xs[i], xs[j] = xs[j], xs[i]
        xs[i + 1:] = xs[i + 1:][::-1]
```
